  "chapter": {
    "number": 22,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Eliphaz: Can a Man Be of Use to God?"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          "Then Eliphaz the Temanite replied:"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“Can a man be of use to God?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Can even a wise man benefit Him?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Does it delight the Almighty that you are righteous?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Does He profit if your ways are blameless?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Is it for your reverence that He rebukes you",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and enters into judgment against you?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Is not your wickedness great?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Are not your iniquities endless?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For you needlessly demanded security from your brothers",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and deprived the naked of their clothing.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "You gave no water to the weary",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and withheld food from the famished,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "while the land belonged to a mighty man,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and a man of honor lived on it.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "You sent widows away empty-handed,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the strength of the fatherless was crushed.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Therefore snares surround you,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and sudden peril terrifies you;",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "it is so dark you cannot see,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and a flood of water covers you.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Is not God as high as the heavens?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Look at the highest stars, how lofty they are!",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Yet you say: ‘What does God know?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Does He judge through thick darkness?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Thick clouds veil Him so He does not see us",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "as He traverses the vault of heaven.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 3179
          },
          {
            "text": "’",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Will you stay on the ancient path",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "that wicked men have trod?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "They were snatched away before their time,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and their foundations were swept away by a flood.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 17,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "They said to God, ‘Depart from us.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "What can the Almighty do to us?’",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 18,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "But it was He who filled their houses with good things;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "so I stay far from the counsel of the wicked.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 19,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The righteous see it and are glad;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the innocent mock them:",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 20,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "‘Surely our foes are destroyed,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and fire has consumed their excess.’",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 21,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Reconcile now and be at peace with Him;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "thereby good will come to you.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 22,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Receive instruction from His mouth,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and lay up His words in your heart.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 23,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "If you return to the Almighty, you will be restored.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "If you remove injustice from your tents",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 24,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "and consign your gold to the dust",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the gold of Ophir to the stones of the ravines,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 25,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "then the Almighty will be your gold",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the finest silver for you.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 26,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Surely then you will delight in the Almighty",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and lift up your face to God.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 27,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "You will pray to Him, and He will hear you,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and you will fulfill your vows.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 28,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Your decisions will be carried out,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and light will shine on your ways.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 29,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "When men are brought low and you say, ‘Lift them up!’",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "then He will save the lowly.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 30,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He will deliver even one who is not innocent,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "rescuing him through the cleanness of your hands.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
